      "type": "html",
      "text": "\n[[Polymorphism And Inheritance]] are certainly patterns that facilitate OO programming, but are these essential to the idea of objects? It's possible to do without them (e.g., perforce in [[Visual Basic For Applications]] and [[Visual Basic]]) and yet program with constructs that model real-world entities. Encapsulation seems to be the key distinction between OO and procedural programming: asking data to do things instead of doing things to data -- [[David Wright]] [<i>Agreed. See [[Object Oriented Discussion]].</i>]",
      "id": "5395d716e0b05dbef3f2853a9c9c6aaa"
